name: Regeneron
tweet: We and our partners have been working as hard as possible to manufacture our investigational #COVID19 antibodies, while ensuring we also deliver our approved and investigational medicines to patients who need them. For more about our team, visit:  https://t.co/NlRFTovCYW

name: Regeneron
tweet: In total, it usually takes about 3-4 months to go from ‚Äòcracking the vial‚Äô to having a medicine that is ready for human use. Throughout the process, operational excellence and patient safety are our top priorities.

name: Regeneron
tweet: Step 6 ‚Äì Filling, Packing & Labeling: These bottles are sent to our fill & finish partners, who put the formulated drug substance into the appropriate vials or syringes. More quality tests are conducted and, finally, the medicines are labeled and packaged for distribution.  https://t.co/6pJqCCtP4K

name: Regeneron
tweet: Step 5 ‚Äì Formulation & Dispensing: Buffers are added to maintain the therapeutic antibody at a desired concentration and ensure stability through the entirety of the drug‚Äôs shelf life.

name: Regeneron
tweet: Step 4 ‚Äì Purification: Next the target #antibodies are further isolated, purified and concentrated in a multi-step process to ensure they are at the appropriate density and of the highest medical-grade quality.  https://t.co/vDTmFIAavq

name: Regeneron
tweet: Step 3 ‚Äì Harvest: About 4-6 weeks after we started, the CHO cells have secreted a large quantity of antibodies & the harvesting process can begin. This separates protein & media from cellular debris, first through centrifugation & then by a sequence of increasingly fine filters.  https://t.co/rDKvT30thL

name: Regeneron
tweet: Our #antibodies are made from living cells, so the environment inside a bioreactor needs to mimic a body ‚Äì warm, full of oxygen & food. But unlike a body, there‚Äôs no immune system, so we also need strict controls and quality checks in place to avoid contamination.

name: Regeneron
tweet: Step 2 ‚Äì Production: Once fully expanded in our largest production vessels, the cells switch from growth mode and start secreting protein (the #antibody).  https://t.co/nfrLfeURHw

name: Regeneron
tweet: Under the watchful eye of our specialists, these cells continue to grow as they are moved to larger & larger controlled bioreactor environments ‚Äì going from a vessel about the size of a soda can to a 10KL stainless steel vat.

name: Regeneron
tweet: Step 1 ‚Äì Cell Line Expansion: The #manufacturing process starts by ‚Äòcracking the vial‚Äô of identical CHO cells which use their energy either to grow or to churn out the desired antibody. As long as they have nutrients and space, CHO cells will stay in growth phase.  https://t.co/1ghtHfWyeg

name: Regeneron
tweet: Producing our #antibody medicines is a complex and time-intensive process. We break down how our #RegeneronIOPS team turns cells into life-changing medicines using the power of #science.  https://t.co/UcqTD5MLeh

name: Regeneron
tweet: 13) We‚Äôre a group of people working as hard as we possibly can to fight this terrible & disruptive disease. It‚Äôs been an unexpected & challenging year for us all, but we‚Äôre optimistic about what we can do by harnessing the power of science.

name: Regeneron
tweet: 12) The U.S. Government will distribute & allocate these ~300K doses & has stated that it is committed to making them available to the American people for free.

name: Regeneron
tweet: 11) The U.S. Government has acquired the initial supply: enough to treat approx. 300K people over the next few months (with ~50K doses ready now), should regulators authorize use.

name: Regeneron
tweet: 10) We started scaling up as early as possible back in April (before we even had data, just in case our studies were successful) & partnered with Roche to significantly expand capacity starting in 2021.

name: Regeneron
tweet: 9) We‚Äôve always been transparent that, if REGN-COV2 is authorized for emergency use, initial supply will be limited despite our significant efforts to ramp up capacity. This is because antibody medicines are complex & time-intensive to make.

name: Regeneron
tweet: 8) Since 2015, we have collaborated with the U.S. Government to apply our technologies & expertise against a range of infectious diseases. In 2020, we have partnered with OWS, HHS, BARDA & NIAID on certain aspects of our COVID & Ebola programs.

name: Regeneron
tweet: 7) HEK293Ts are commercially available & very commonly used by research labs. They have been involved in the development of important vaccines & therapeutics for conditions such as hemophilias A/B & Type 2 diabetes. Original literature is available here:  https://t.co/HUFTu5pHvJ

name: Regeneron
tweet: 6) Of the many experiments in our COVID-19 program, one involved using the HEK293T cell line to help us select potent virus-neutralizing antibodies. HEK293T is a 40+ year old ‚Äòimmortalized‚Äô cell line that was originally derived from embryonic kidney cells in the 1970s.

name: Regeneron
tweet: 5) We did not use human stem cells or human embryonic stem cells in our COVID-19 program. Like many other science-focused organizations, we do use these tools in a responsible & limited manner for certain early research. More here:  https://t.co/ezkgl4Or2a

name: Regeneron
tweet: 4) We also invented a completely different antibody combination for #Ebola that was just approved by the FDA earlier this month.

name: Regeneron
tweet: 3) Our investigational antibody combination therapy (known as ‚ÄòREGN-COV2‚Äô) is currently being tested in clinical trials. It was invented this year using our proprietary technologies that were developed over the course of 30 years.

name: Regeneron
tweet: 2) Regeneron is the name of our company ‚Äì we make many different medicines for many serious diseases & have been around for 30+ years. We are a group of about 9K people, many of us scientists, MDs and/or engineers. More here:  https://t.co/7lgFQDO6Ik

name: Regeneron
tweet: @SciImmunology Our data help paint a picture of how allergic memory arises with allergen exposure ‚Äì and why severe allergy can persist for decades in certain people, even in the absence of allergen re-exposure

name: Regeneron
tweet: @SciImmunology This type of IgE can then respond to the allergen and induce anaphylaxis, a potentially life-threatening allergic reaction

name: Regeneron
tweet: @SciImmunology Our team found that prolonged allergen exposure led to accumulation of long-lived IgE plasma cells in the bone marrow thus establishing allergen memory by producing allergen-specific IgE that circulates through the body (in humans & mice)
